    <p>Dr. Robert Lustig is a pediatric neuroendocrinologist who has spent decades researching the effects of sugar on metabolic health. His 2009 lecture "Sugar: The Bitter Truth" became a viral phenomenon, bringing scientific understanding of fructose metabolism to millions.</p>

    <p>His work focuses on how processed food, particularly sugar and fructose, drives metabolic disease independent of calories. He has been a vocal critic of the food industry and has advocated for regulatory approaches to address the obesity and diabetes epidemics.</p>
